commit.message:
test: use unique output file names across tests

Without the change tests ran in parallel occasionally clobber outputs of
one another and fail as:

    $ make check -j16 VERBOSE=y
    ...
    FAIL: huge
    ==========
    Converting
    File ../test/data/5.plist is open
    PList XML parsing succeeded
    PList BIN writing succeeded
    PList BIN parsing succeeded
    PList XML writing succeeded
    Size of input and output is different
    Input size : 4292380
    Output size : 4305301
    Comparing
    PList parsing failed
    FAIL huge.test (exit status: 3)

Closes: https://github.com/libimobiledevice/libplist/issues/234#issuecomment-1743820556

Prevent adding NULL items to array/dictionary nodes

Thanks to @tihmstar for pointing this out!

Plug memory leak in plist_write_to_stream()

Thanks @beyonik for pointing this out!
Add explicit casts and fix return type mismatches
Add an explicit PLIST_FORMAT_NONE value
autoconf: Remove unused function checks and fix constructor/destructor attribute check

bplist: Move realloc from parse_unicode_node() into plist_utf16be_to_utf8()

It is very confusing to handle the reallocation (buffer shrinking)
outside of the actual conversion function.
Make sure function signatures match their declarations in the public header
Windows: Use winsock2.h instead of sys/time.h when using MSVC
Add space before PRI* macros, some compilers do not like it
Move PLIST_API to the headers
Silence another false 'shadows builtin function' warning on MinGW
